In [181]:
#definie lag
lags = 5
In [183]:
#creat list and append all lag return to the cols list
cols = []
for lag in range(1, lags + 1):
    #creat title for data frame
    col = 'lag{}'.format(lag)
    #create data fram with given title for lag, also creat lag
    data[col] = data.returns.shift(lag)
    #append the given col name lag{} to cols list
    cols.append(col)
    
#droping missing values 
data.dropna(inplace = True)

#create lags 
lags = 5

#create empty list to store lags name
cols = []

#for loop to create column for given lags
for lag in range(1, lags + 1):
    #create column name 
    col = 'lag{}'.format(lag)
    #create the column on given data frame
    data[col] = data.returns.shift(lag)
    #append the col list name to cols
    cols.append(col)

#droping missing values
data.dropna(inplace = True)
data
